<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-19T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="815" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 841.711/349</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d815fn1">The same to the
                                Ambassador in France as No. 1615, referring to No. 1528, May 25,
                                which is not printed.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-19T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3538. Department’s 3363, May 25.<note n="2" xml:id="d815fn2">Not
                                printed.</note> Department has received no answer to or
                            acknowledgment of its notes of May 24<note n="3" xml:id="d815fn3">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_604">p.
                                604</ref>.</note> to the British and French Ambassadors regarding
                            censorship of mails, substance of which Department cabled you on May 25.
                            You may press for an immediate reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>